## Documentation Organization

When creating or updating DocC documentation:
1. Determine if content is **package-level** (protocol APIs, reusable) or **app-level** (integration, platform-specific)
2. See `documentation-principles.mdc` for detailed guidelines, and `documentation-macOS-app.mdc` for macOS app article specifics
3. Follow the package vs app documentation separation principle

**Rule**: Package APIs go in package Documentation.docc/, app integration goes in app Documentation.docc/
